    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c74f40e2_3a1ce0b9",
        "filename": "buildbucket/cmd/bb/log.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 265,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-28T23:58:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve noticed a condition (likely race condition in the butler) where timeoffsets for some streams aren\u0027t always populated for the first log chunk.\n(root cause of https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id\u003d908436)\nThis means in some very rare conditions, if timestamp is used for ordering, the ordering of the lines in the first chunk between streams may be unstable.\n\nTo mitigate this, the PrefixIndex can be used for ordering instead.",
      "revId": "39c2a90c033a99a7dce42c6ab9c744eab4dc8708",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b6006e8d_7b6f4146",
        "filename": "buildbucket/cmd/bb/log.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 265,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-29T00:29:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "PrefixIndex says\n\n\u003e It is used to designate unambiguous log\n    // ordering.\n\ncan we always use it and not bother with offset then? it would be much simpler",
      "parentUuid": "c74f40e2_3a1ce0b9",
      "revId": "39c2a90c033a99a7dce42c6ab9c744eab4dc8708",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f390ad0a_22f4a34d",
        "filename": "buildbucket/cmd/bb/log.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 265,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-29T17:12:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, in general PrefixIndex has guarantees set by butler, and should always be used for ordering within a prefix (which is what this log subcommand is doing)",
      "parentUuid": "b6006e8d_7b6f4146",
      "revId": "39c2a90c033a99a7dce42c6ab9c744eab4dc8708",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ed54715e_601083d2",
        "filename": "buildbucket/cmd/bb/log.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 265,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-29T17:29:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "thinking about this more... i remember there were ideas to accept user-provided log timestamps. In this sense, it is better to use the offset since it may be provided by the user. PrefixIndex cannot be provided by the user. In this case, using time offset is more correct.\n\nHow realistic is the problem here? If it is only the first chunk, presumably it matches the stream creation timestamp, and that\u0027s what PS3 is doing: adds offset only if it is present",
      "parentUuid": "f390ad0a_22f4a34d",
      "revId": "39c2a90c033a99a7dce42c6ab9c744eab4dc8708",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ed1283c9_dd2b487f",
        "filename": "buildbucket/cmd/bb/log.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 265,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-29T22:42:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think it\u0027s a huge issue.\n\nImagine this - We try to multiplex 20 streams.  The butler ingests them at distinct times, but for whatever reason (let\u0027s say they\u0027re user provided log timestamps), all timestamps are 0 offsets.  All lines in all 20 streams have the same timestamp.\nNow, in this case, using timestamps, there is no defined order between the different streams.  I think in the current implementation they will probably be stable because the streams have a defined order between themselves (ie not in a map).\n\nThat being said, I think this will only be a problem in pathological cases, and isn\u0027t something we should be too worried about.",
      "parentUuid": "ed54715e_601083d2",
      "revId": "39c2a90c033a99a7dce42c6ab9c744eab4dc8708",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "158bc776_ccc821e9",
        "filename": "buildbucket/cmd/bb/log.go",
